<l>namava veṉṉu mūṉṟoṭu civaṇi</l>
<l>yakaram variṉu meṭṭaṉmu ṉiyalpē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>There is no change [in the rules mentioned] concerning <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṭṭu</foreign> ' eight '</l>
<l>when the three [sounds] <foreign xml:lang="ta">n, m</foreign> [and] <foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign> combine [with <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṭṭu</foreign>].<note place="foot">I.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṭ</foreign> of <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṭṭu</foreign>
          is replaced by <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṇ,</foreign> eg. <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṇṇāḻi,
          eṇmaṇṭai, eṇvaṭṭi, eṇṇakal.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
